<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1745,2024]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,153,611]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,1817,1844]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Description. Male</emphasis>
. 
<figureCitation box="[429,496,1817,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, whole fly. Head as 
<figureCitation box="[733,802,1817,1843]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, with the frons lacking microtrichia except at its edges. Cheek with 5 bristles and jowl with 2 that are longer and more robust. Postpedicels, which lack SPS vesicles, palps and proboscis from below as 
<figureCitation box="[488,557,1889,1915]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
. Thorax brown, with 3 notopleural bristles and no cleft in front of these, and mesopleuron with hairs (
<figureCitation box="[429,498,1925,1951]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Scutellum with an anterior pair of hairs and a posterior pair of bristles. Abdominal tergites and venter as 
<figureCitation box="[406,476,1961,1988]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
. Hypopygium as 
<figureCitation box="[682,784,1961,1987]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Figs 6–8</figureCitation>
, with left hypandrial lobe having microtrichia projecting from its tip (
<figureCitation box="[293,362,1997,2024]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). The right lobe is vestigial. Fore tarsus with posterodorsal hair palisade on segments 1–4 (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) and its basitarsus with rows of spinules ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[747,831,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Dorsal hair palisade of mid tibia extends about 0.63 times its length. Hind femur as 
<figureCitation box="[498,578,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–11" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1752,1777]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,186,1720]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1393,181,1726]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1–11. Megaselia ajabshirensis n. sp. male. 1, whole fly; 2, head; 3, postpedicels, palps and proboscis; 4, side of thorax; 5, abdomen; 6–8, hypopygium; 9, front tarsus; 10, front basitarsus; 11, hind femur. Scale bars 20 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573368/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
. Hind tibia with 15–16 moderately differentiated posterodorsal hairs, without anterodorsals, and spinules of apical combs simple. Wings 
<quantity box="[823,924,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.36" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="1.36">1.36 mm</quantity>
long, light gray with thick veins light brown and thin veins pale gray. Costal index 0.39. Costal ratios 4.1: 1.1: 1. Costal cilia (of section 3) 
<quantity box="[1230,1331,261,287]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="0.08">0.08 mm</quantity>
long. No hair at base of vein 3. With 2 axillary bristles, the outer one being 
<quantity box="[892,992,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
long. Sc not reaching R1. Haltere knob brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,611]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,349,368,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Recognition.</emphasis>
In the key the British species (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[706,852,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref21228" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1989) Scuttle Flies-Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects, 10 (8), 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) it runs to couplet 87. The hypopygium of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wood)" authorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityName="Wood" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">M. conformis</emphasis>
(Wood)
</taxonomicName>
has short hairs on the epandrium. The palps of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lundbeck)" authorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityName="Lundbeck" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[852,1151,405,432]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripalpis">
<emphasis box="[852,1013,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">M. nigripalpis</emphasis>
(Lundbeck)
</taxonomicName>
are brown and its cosrtal index exceeds 0.45. A further 8 Palaearctic species will run to the same couplet. Most are excluded by having more than 2 axillary bristles, brown palps and/or costal index exceeding 0.45. Of the rest the dorsal edge of the epandrium is sub-equal in length to the ventral edge in contrast to our new species. Non Palaearctic species are likewise excluded.
</paragraph>
